webpackJsonp([0x8300c3f50a73],{397:function(a,n){a.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{author:"Martin",homeCity:"Internationally"}},markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Last year, Microsoft has introduced <em>“Windows Subsystem for Linux”</em> (WSL) onto Windows 10 - 64 bit edition. It was primarily targeted at open source developers who needed to develop on Windows, but were required to use command line tools which were developed for *nix first. Additionally, owing to the large differences between Windows and *nix filesystems, creating a Windows port for these projects was a low priority given the rapid development. A good example of this is <a href="https://www.tensorflow.org">Tensorflow</a> where releases pre-1.0.0 did not have a windows release. Since the API has stabilised, and there is money to be made across platforms, Google has since created a Windows install path. </p>\n<p>The release of .NET Core has opened up a world of new possibilities for developers previously limited to the Windows ecosystem. Applications developed with .NET Core can also be deployed on popular Linux distributions. The catch is that former Windows only developers need now to up their *nix game…</p>\n<p>WSL is a good starting point. Here’s how to get started…</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Open the Windows Settings application, and select the <strong><em>Update and Security</em></strong> option.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-8dc3d.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 106.69800235017625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Windows Settings"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/WindowsSettings-45629bc42f47f21df47106c702e3f46f-8dc3d.png 851w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Select <strong>For Developers</strong> and switch <em>Developer Mode</em> on.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-8dc3d.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 106.69800235017625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="For Developers"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/ForDevelopers-3b3c8d0bd5a35acb29c58020b0472e40-8dc3d.png 851w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Open the windows <strong>Control Panel</strong> and select <em>Programs and Features</em>. Add the Linux Subsystem feature as shown.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash0-5bb94b41b72b78967a5bc129aceb8ba8-d9cc8.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 543px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 98.52670349907919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Programs and Features"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash0-5bb94b41b72b78967a5bc129aceb8ba8-d9cc8.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash0-5bb94b41b72b78967a5bc129aceb8ba8-54a2d.png 148w,\n/static/bash0-5bb94b41b72b78967a5bc129aceb8ba8-79bbb.png 295w,\n/static/bash0-5bb94b41b72b78967a5bc129aceb8ba8-d9cc8.png 543w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 543px) 100vw, 543px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nAfter selecting OK, Windows will need to reboot.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Following the reboot, select the “Bash” option from the start menu. It will be faster to type-to-search for the command then to dig it out of the menus.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash1-d81f2546049a5bc7794c1a1381ab9a36-e2f61.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 393px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 158.52417302798983%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Start Menu"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash1-d81f2546049a5bc7794c1a1381ab9a36-e2f61.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash1-d81f2546049a5bc7794c1a1381ab9a36-a8e4b.png 148w,\n/static/bash1-d81f2546049a5bc7794c1a1381ab9a36-a2c5d.png 295w,\n/static/bash1-d81f2546049a5bc7794c1a1381ab9a36-e2f61.png 393w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 393px) 100vw, 393px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>A command prompt will open with a URL:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-7c491.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 50.303030303030305%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Command Prompt - URL"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash2-db07f26d3db5f3b25b43cf6f4f47848a-7c491.png 660w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nOpening the URL will in-turn open a windows store page offering a choice of Linux distributions to install.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-6a8b3.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 77.25392886683208%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Windows Store - Linux Distros"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-526de.png 885w,\n/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/bash3-f50fe62e4f883673ee818d2c79793b64-6a8b3.png 1209w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>For this demonstration we’ll install Ubuntu.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-6a8b3.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 77.25392886683208%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Ubuntu"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-526de.png 885w,\n/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/bash4-d806b00af77918661f68e67b5db4dd11-6a8b3.png 1209w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>After selecting the <strong>GET</strong> button Ubuntu will begin the download and install - approx 195Mb.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-a7964.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 50.3793626707132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Ubuntu"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash5-54952b430f2d4b70325aa578ecdd7198-a7964.png 659w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You’ll be prompted for a new username and password for the Linux Subsystem</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-a7964.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 50.3793626707132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="New user and password"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash6-ded43b760a65fa912fc985d4aa17080a-a7964.png 659w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>And we’re ready to go…</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-a7964.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 50.3793626707132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Ready"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash7-4ad48617366c1658962c8e07cc65892f-a7964.png 659w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Your familiar windows drives can be found from the root directory as: <code>/mnt/c</code> etc.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-a7964.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 50.3793626707132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Windows Drives"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/bash8-76e42ce3869538ea562d83111c46d4cd-a7964.png 659w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In a future article we’ll see what we can do with this beyond standard linux file management.</p>',excerpt:"Last year, Microsoft has introduced  “Windows Subsystem for Linux”  (WSL) onto Windows 10 - 64 bit edition. It was primarily targeted at…",fields:{tagSlugs:["/tags/windows-10/","/tags/linux/","/tags/subsystem/"]},frontmatter:{title:"Windows 10 has a Linux Subsystem",tags:["windows 10","linux","subsystem"],date:"January 31, 2018"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/linux-subsystem-on-win10/"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---linux-subsystem-on-win-10-9bacf7fc6c0fbd4702b0.js.map